Will be back many more times

name: Warna Kedaton Hotel and Meetings
address: Jl. Jaya Giri Utara No.1, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80236, Indonesia
review 1:
Cheap and reachable. Not quite clean bathrooms.
I first got a room for 4 beds and the AC wasn't cold at all. Then i asked for a change, and they don't have an idea what to do cause all of the 4 beds room are full. Then, I asked for 3 beds room + 1 extra bed. The new room's faucet wasn't working but too lazy to ask them again.
No towel, no lift, old hotel with old furniture and AC except for the 4th floor which is too tiring to go there with stairs.
review 2: Comments do not honor this hotel. Good stay while we are renovating our visa (25 min walk to imm office). Pool was perfect after profiting the day outside, room was verified to be clean even before being handed with the keys, ac operational. True there are things to improve, but keep in mind is an old hotel adapting to modern tendencies (seems is accepted to be sourrounded by insects in a 5 star hotel in the middle of the jungle for 10 times the price, but not a single mosquitoe here is allowed).
review 3: Basic service like towel, soap, etc weren't provided. We asked and staff said they would deliver to our room, but they never came. We asked again and they said all towels were being laundered. Heard another guest next to our room complained about the exact same thing. Not even mineral bottled waters were served. At night I couldn't sleep because I felt annoying itches all over my body. I turned the lamp back on and was utterly shocked to find out dozens of BEDBUGS crawling all over the bed. We immediately checked out the morning after.
review 4: I stayed here when I went to Bali, it's actually very far from the beach and not close to the Kuta area. There is a nice local roadside food stall outside. Staff is rarely around and worst of all, the bathtub was stopped up! The room is big but not in good shape, don't expect a nice hotel or one that's easy to find. My taxi driver couldn't find it and I had to walk up and down the street six times before I could. If you rent a motorbike which I finally did it made it better, I think a motorbike was 50,000IDR which is very cheap
review 5:
I rarely writes about a bad things.
Just to a few say.
If you need just a bed to sleep and on low budget this the hotel for you.
Big old hotel with spacious room.
Don't aspects any good services.
I booked this hotel just because is very near to Taman Werdhi Arts Centre. I spent my whole day enjoying the 2018 Bali Arts Festival for 2 days. Room just for me to sleep.

name: Taman Kopi Bali

review 1:

The place is quite secluded with a relatively small road.
review 2: Taman Kopi Bali is a hidden gem that offers an exceptional coffee experience. With its inviting atmosphere, superb coffee selection, delectable treats, and attentive service, it has all the ingredients for a memorable visit. If you're a coffee aficionado or simply seeking a haven to relax and enjoy a cup of coffee, this place should be at the top of your list.
review 3: The place is really good for hang out with your friend until midnight. Surprisingly cheap. Rum regal was great.
review 4: the place is so cozy and not to loud because it a bit far from main road. The menu is okay.
review 5: I like the chocolate caramel. The owner is my friend at campus hahaha.. He really to open this cafe.

address: Jl. Jaya Giri No.15, Dangin Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
Didn't have a high expectations on this place, but it was worth it. First time coming here.

The service is good, can't complain i guess.

Ordered hainan rice and chili oil noodles.
The vanilla ice tea was great. The coffee was okay.

Noodles was really great, the broth was really good üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç.  Nasi bakmoy was really unexpected that they plate in on a bowl.
But overall the taste was good that i can't complain Definitely taste the hainan.
Definitely order some pangsit or side dish if you come here.
And they have jumbo size for some of the menu for the big eaters.
They got indoor and outdoor seating, places is definitely on the small side but its good.

gonna come here again, i recommend this place if you're craving some legit chicken noodles.

Thank you.
review 2:
